# PULSAR

GPU queue and fairness control plane for shared Kubernetes clusters.

PULSAR sits between job submission and GPU execution. It queues workloads, enforces per-team quotas, schedules based on configurable fairness policies, and **spawns REAL GPU processes** (visible in `nvidia-smi`) with `nvidia.com/gpu` resource requests.

When Kubernetes isn't available, it runs standalone — same scheduling logic, processes spawn on the local host.

**Key Principle:** Each scheduled job corresponds to an actual OS process consuming GPU memory. No simulation. No mock execution. Real `nvidia-smi` output.

