## Running PULSAR

### Starting the Server

```bash
# Activate venv first
source venv/bin/activate

# Navigate to src directory
cd src

# Start the API server (listens on http://0.0.0.0:8080)
python -m pulsar.cli server
```

**Server Output Example:**

```
INFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8080
INFO:     Application startup complete
```

### Submitting Your First Job

**In another terminal:**

```bash
# Activate venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Submit a job (4 GPUs, team-a user)
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli submit -u team-a -g 4

# Check job status
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli jobs

# Show cluster status
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli cluster
```

### Job Workflow Example

```bash
# 1. Submit a job
JOB_ID=$(cd src && python -m pulsar.cli submit -u team-a -g 2 | grep -oP 'job-\d+')

# 2. Check status
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli jobs -u team-a

# 3. View cluster utilization
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli cluster

# 4. View fairness metrics
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli fairness

# 5. Cancel a job (if needed)
cd src && python -m pulsar.cli cancel $JOB_ID
```

