## CLI

The `pulsar` command-line tool provides full control over job submission, monitoring, and cluster management.

### Server Management

```bash
pulsar server                         # Start API server (http://0.0.0.0:8080)
```

**Environment variables:**

```bash
PULSAR_HOST=0.0.0.0 PULSAR_PORT=8080 pulsar server
```

### Job Management

```bash
# Submit a job
pulsar submit -u team-a -g 4                    # 4 GPUs, team-a
pulsar submit -u team-a -g 2 -p HIGH            # 2 GPUs, HIGH priority
pulsar submit -u team-b -g 1 -p CRITICAL        # Preemptible

# List jobs with filtering
pulsar jobs                                      # All jobs
pulsar jobs -u team-a                           # By user
pulsar jobs -u team-a -s RUNNING                # By user and status
pulsar jobs -s QUEUED                           # By status only
pulsar jobs --format json                       # JSON output

# Job details
pulsar jobs <job-id>                            # Get details for one job

# Job control
pulsar cancel <job-id>                          # Cancel a job
pulsar complete <job-id>                        # Mark job as completed
```

### Cluster and Resource Management

```bash
# Cluster status
pulsar cluster                                  # GPU utilization, topology
pulsar cluster --format json                    # JSON output

# Queue status
pulsar queues                                   # Per-user queue depths

# Quota management
pulsar quotas                                   # List all quotas
pulsar quotas team-a                            # Get team-a quota
pulsar quotas -u team-a --max-gpus 10           # Set team-a max GPUs
pulsar quotas -u team-a --max-jobs 5            # Set team-a max concurrent jobs
```

### Monitoring and Metrics

```bash
# Fairness metrics
pulsar fairness                                 # Per-team fairness report
pulsar fairness --jain                          # Include Jain's index

# Prometheus metrics
pulsar metrics                                  # Dump Prometheus-format metrics

# System health
pulsar health                                   # Liveness and readiness probes
```

### Help

```bash
pulsar --help                                   # General help
pulsar submit --help                            # Help for specific command
```

