```

### Component Responsibilities

| Component | Language | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| **PULSAR** | Python | GPU job queuing, fair-share scheduling, quota enforcement, preemption |
| **Scheduler** | Go | Kubernetes scheduler plugin for topology-aware placement |
| **Optimizer** | Python | ML-based workload optimization and resource prediction |
| **Discovery** | Go | Automatic GPU and node topology discovery |
| **MIG Controller** | Go | NVIDIA MIG (Multi-Instance GPU) partitioning |
| **Cost Engine** | Go | GPU cost tracking and billing |
| **Exporter** | Go | Prometheus metrics export from GPU metrics |
| **Node Agent** | Go | Per-node monitoring and health checks |

### Data Flow

```
User/Driver → PULSAR API (FastAPI)
   ↓
Job submission → Queue Manager
   ↓
Fair Scheduler (score users) → Admission Controller (check quotas)
   ↓
Preemption (if needed) ↔ Executor
   ↓
K8s Job Creation / Standalone Execution
   ↓
Persistence Layer (SQLite) → Prometheus Metrics
   ↓
Dashboard / API / CLI
```

### Core PULSAR Components

The PULSAR layer sits on top of the existing KGWE scheduling infrastructure:

- **`src/scheduler/`** — Go scheduler plugin handles topology-aware GPU placement
- **`src/optimizer/`** — Python ML optimizer for workload optimization
- **`src/discovery/`** — GPU and node topology discovery

PULSAR adds:

- **Job queuing** per user/team (FIFO)
- **Fair-share scheduling** with weighted priority
- **Quota enforcement** (max GPUs + concurrent jobs per team)
- **Preemption** for priority jobs
- **Multiple scheduling policies** (FIFO, Fair Share, Priority, Backfill)
- **REST API** and **CLI** for easy access
- **Monitoring** with Prometheus metrics and Grafana dashboards
- **Persistence** with SQLite for job history

### Key Files for Development

**Control Plane:**

- **Main entry point:** [src/pulsar/cli.py](src/pulsar/cli.py) — CLI and server startup
- **Core orchestration:** [src/pulsar/control_plane.py](src/pulsar/control_plane.py) — Wires all components
- **Queue management:** [src/pulsar/queue_manager.py](src/pulsar/queue_manager.py) — Per-team FIFO queues
- **Scheduling logic:** [src/pulsar/fair_scheduler.py](src/pulsar/fair_scheduler.py) — Fair-share scoring
- **Admission control:** [src/pulsar/admission_controller.py](src/pulsar/admission_controller.py) — Quota enforcement

**Execution Layer (CRITICAL):**

- **Job executor:** [src/pulsar/executor.py](src/pulsar/executor.py) — Spawns real GPU processes, manages PIDs
- **GPU worker:** `src/pulsar/gpu_worker.py` — Code that jobs run (allocates GPU, runs compute)
- **Preemption engine:** [src/pulsar/preemption.py](src/pulsar/preemption.py) — Kills processes on preemption

**Interface & Monitoring:**

- **REST API:** [src/pulsar/api_server.py](src/pulsar/api_server.py) — FastAPI endpoints
- **Metrics:** [src/pulsar/metrics.py](src/pulsar/metrics.py) — Prometheus integration
- **Dashboard:** [src/pulsar/dashboard.py](src/pulsar/dashboard.py) — Web UI

**Infrastructure:**

- **Persistence:** [src/pulsar/persistence.py](src/pulsar/persistence.py) — SQLite job store with PID tracking
- **Testing:** [tests/test_pulsar.py](tests/test_pulsar.py) — 38+ test cases
- **Config:** [src/pulsar/pulsar.yaml](src/pulsar/pulsar.yaml) — Default settings

