## Docker Deployment

### Build Docker Image

```bash
# Build PULSAR image
docker build -t pulsar:latest -f docker/Dockerfile.pulsar .

# Tag and push to registry
docker tag pulsar:latest myregistry/pulsar:latest
docker push myregistry/pulsar:latest
```

### Run in Docker

```bash
# Run standalone (without Kubernetes)
docker run -d \
  --name pulsar \
  -p 8080:8080 \
  -v /tmp/pulsar.db:/pulsar.db \
  pulsar:latest

# Check logs
docker logs -f pulsar

# Access dashboard
# http://localhost:8080/

# Stop container
docker stop pulsar
```

### Docker Compose (Optional)

For a complete stack with monitoring:

```yaml
# Create docker-compose.yaml
version: '3.8'
services:
  pulsar:
    image: pulsar:latest
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
    volumes:
      - pulsar-db:/pulsar.db
    environment:
      PULSAR_LOGGING_LEVEL: INFO

  prometheus:
    image: prom/prometheus:latest
    ports:
      - "9090:9090"
    volumes:
      - ./prometheus.yaml:/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yaml
    command:
      - '--config.file=/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yaml'

  grafana:
    image: grafana/grafana:latest
    ports:
      - "3000:3000"
    depends_on:
      - prometheus

volumes:
  pulsar-db:
```

```bash
# Start stack
docker-compose up -d

# View logs
docker-compose logs -f pulsar

# Stop stack
docker-compose down
```

